o keep this mod working for KSP.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nerfclasher","CreatedById":158707,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-12T20:44:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222848221\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002284938\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221478979756\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110546\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022westamastaflash\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, westamastaflash said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/130617-jrodriguez/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022130617\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/130617-jrodriguez/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@jrodriguez\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Want to take over CT permanently? I was maintaining it mostly because of Time Control. I am moving house over the next two months so won\u0027t have time to do any code updates.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI made a pr to save you time\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Draconiator","CreatedById":133772,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-14T18:13:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhere are the camera parts in 1.2.1?\u00A0 I looked everywhere but can\u0027t find them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"V8jester","CreatedById":136093,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-14T18:18:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222850502\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002284938\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221479147234\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022133772\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Draconiator\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Draconiator said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhere are the camera parts in 1.2.1?\u00A0 I looked everywhere but can\u0027t find them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWrong mod. That sounds like\u00A0HullCam VDS.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCameraTools has no parts. Just a plugin and a GUI for Filming with a moving\u00A0camera angle.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Draconiator","CreatedById":133772,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-14T21:25:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAh, oops, them maybe I have the wrong one then...I love being able to set up the exact shot lol\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Azimech","CreatedById":50750,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-15T17:37:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt works! Thanks guys!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s just one little thing ... The absolutely most fabulous part of Camera Tools is the doppler effect. I\u0027m not sure it\u0027s in a released version but if it\u0027s so, it\u0027s not working anymore. I have a 1.05 unreleased dev build with it.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nIf it can be implemented or repaired, you\u0027d make a lot of movie makers extremely happy!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/KK8a6aqC8Qc?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-11-15T17:39:58Z\u0022 title=\u002211/15/2016 05:39  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 15, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Azimech\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DAL1189","CreatedById":58027,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-21T20:36:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes this mod require an update for 1.2.2?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ThiccRocketScientist","CreatedById":135273,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-23T05:47:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEech, I\u0027m getting an anomaly with the Camera tools patch. Every time I use the camera, when reverting to normal position to control it focuses on the root part (i.e. the probe top of the rocket)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a solution or setting to disable this?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJohn\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jebs_SY","CreatedById":169510,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-24T00:17:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222898095\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002284938\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221482472036\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022135273\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022John The Physicist\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 hours ago, John The Physicist said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m getting an anomaly with the Camera tools patch. Every time I use the camera, when reverting to normal position to control it focuses on the root part (i.e. the probe top of the rocket)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can confirm this. After using camera tools the camera focus goes to the root part, not the center of mass.\u003Cbr\u003E\nWhen right clicking the root part, it also says \u0022Reset Camera\u0022 and not \u0022Aim Camera\u0022 so the focus is indeed \u0022officially\u0022 on the root part.\u003Cbr\u003E\nWould be nice if we can change that back to Center of Mass = No part focussed. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-12-24T00:47:14Z\u0022 title=\u002212/24/2016 12:47  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 24, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Jebs_SY\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xiphosura","CreatedById":172322,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-01T05:25:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222899046\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002284938\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221482538637\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022169510\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jebs_SY\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 24/12/2016 at 10:17 AM, Jebs_SY said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfter using camera tools the camera focus goes to the root part, not the center of mass.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI get the same issue, but also when switching between craft.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"WanderingKid","CreatedById":110855,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-05T03:39:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey all, my google-fu is failing me for this mod.\u00A0 I\u0027m trying to figure out how to use pathing, and I can\u0027t seem to find any instructions on it.\u00A0 If I missed it somewhere in this thread can you please tell me which page it\u0027s hiding in, otherwise if someone can point me in the right direction for a tutorial or explanation, I\u0027d appreciate it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wren","CreatedById":99277,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-13T15:46:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222899046\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002284938\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221482538637\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022169510\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jebs_SY\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/23/2016 at 6:17 PM, Jebs_SY said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can confirm this. After using camera tools the camera focus goes to the root part, not the center of mass.\u003Cbr\u003E\nWhen right clicking the root part, it also says \u0022Reset Camera\u0022 and not \u0022Aim Camera\u0022 so the focus is indeed \u0022officially\u0022 on the root part.\u003Cbr\u003E\nWould be nice if we can change that back to Center of Mass = No part focussed. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI also get a warning that the mod is not compatible on the main start screen of KSP.\u00A0 Also the part focusing after stopping to camera tool.\u00A0 Other than that I love this mod.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"V8jester","CreatedById":136093,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-13T16:46:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222920290\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002284938\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221484322382\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002299277\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Wren\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n59 minutes ago, Wren said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI also get a warning that the mod is not compatible on the main start screen of KSP.\u00A0 Also the part focusing after stopping to camera tool.\u00A0 Other than that I love this mod.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre you using the lates Caretaker release by \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/130617-jrodriguez/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022130617\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/130617-jrodriguez/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@jrodriguez\u003C/a\u003E?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/jrodrigv/CameraTools/releases\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/jrodrigv/CameraTools/releases\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wren","CreatedById":99277,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-13T17:08:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclas